# Objective

Continue the Structured Component Architecture introduced in Phase 7C.

This slice focuses exclusively on migrating the Homepage Statistics section into a reusable CMS-aware Blade component while preserving the project's enterprise CMS philosophy.

This is **NOT** a visual redesign.

This is **NOT** a page-builder implementation.

This is **NOT** a change to the page hierarchy.

The goal is simply to replace duplicated homepage markup with a reusable structured component that consumes existing CMS-managed content.

---

# Architectural Principles

Read and comply with every instruction contained within the `.claude` directory before making changes.

This implementation **must** remain consistent with:

- CLAUDE.md
- PROJECT.md
- Decision 002 — CMS Architecture
- Decision 005 — AI Guardrails

The project architecture is now officially defined as:

> Public pages are composed of reusable developer-defined Blade components.
>
> Component content is CMS-managed.
>
> Component composition remains developer-controlled.
>
> Administrators may edit content, media, configuration, and visibility only where explicitly supported.
>
> Administrators cannot create arbitrary page layouts or drag-and-drop page structures.

This architectural decision is locked.

Do not introduce any implementation that conflicts with it.

